## 🚨 Red Flags (Automatic BLOCKERS)

If any of these exist, they are **blocking** until fixed:
- Any `TODO` or `FIXME` in production code
- `console.log` in production paths (unless explicitly allowed and guarded)
- Empty `try/catch` blocks
- Endpoints/mutations without auth checks (where applicable)
- DB tables without RLS (if using Postgres/Supabase patterns)
- Forms without validation (server + client side as appropriate)
- `// @ts-ignore` or blanket `eslint-disable` without justification
- Hardcoded secrets/API keys
- Failing tests
- Linter/type errors
- Build warnings treated as regressions
- Missing loading/error/empty states for user-facing flows

